<p>I have the following code (jade)</p>  <pre><code>script(type="text/ng-template" id="carousel.html")     include carousel.html </code></pre>  <p>Where carousel.html has a recursively nested list:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;ul&gt;     &lt;li ng-repeat="step in steps"&gt;         {{step}}         &lt;ul ng-include="'substeps'"&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;     &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Where substeps is:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;script type="text/ng-template" id="substeps"&gt;     &lt;li ng-repeat="step in step.substeps&gt;         {{step}}         &lt;ul ng-include="'substeps'"&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;     &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Basically as long as there are substeps, the ng-repeat will add them as nested lists. This works in all browsers except for IE8. Is there anything I'm overlooking? Maybe a bug in ng-template in IE8?</p>